OL,3,CBritish Museum calls for donations to
OL,4,Csave Tudor pendant linked to Henry VIII
OL,6,FHenry VIII regularly commissioned
OL,7,FLondon goldsmiths to create costume
OL,8,Fjewellery for major celebrations and
OL,9,Fstate occasions which were worn
OL,10,Fbriefly by members of the court to
OL,11,Fcreate the impression of great
OL,12,Fsplendour, according to the British
OL,13,FMuseum.
OL,15,FThe pendant unites the Tudor rose with
OL,16,FKatherine's pomegranate symbol, and
OL,17,Ffeatures a banner that reads
OL,18,F"tousiors", the old French for
OL,19,F"always".
